"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385763","Leader of the House","false","2015-06-30","<p>Over the five years of the last Parliament, the Government introduced 20 bills, the provisions of which did not extend to Scotland. It should be noted that this analysis does not include bills containing provisions of a minor or consequential nature.<br><br>These were as follows:<br><br><strong>2010-2012</strong><br><br>Local Government Finance Bill<br>Academies Bill<br>Charities Bill<br>Education Bill<br>Local Government Bill<br>Localism Bill<br>Police (Detention and Bail) Bill<br>Sunday Trading (London Olympic Games and Paralympic Games) Bill<br>Water Industry (FInancial Assistance) BIll<br><br><strong>2012-2013</strong><br><br>Defamation Bill<br>Jobseekers (Back to Work) Schemes Bill<br>Mental Health (Approval Functions) Bill<br><br><strong>2013-2014</strong><br><br>Criminal Justice &amp; Courts Bill<br>High Speed Rail (London - West Midlands) Bill<br>Local Audit and Accountability Bill<br>Northern Ireland Bill<br>Rehabilitation Bill<br>Wales Bill<br><br><strong>2014-2015</strong><br><br>Modern Slavery Bill<br>Social Action &amp; Heroism Bill</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2015-06-30T12:10:57.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385763/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385763/answer",,,,,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2015-06-25","Government Bills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, which government bills introduced in each of the last five years the provisions of which have not extended to Scotland.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","4229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385764","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-01","<p>The Treasury and HM Revenue and Customs published research analysing the dynamic effects of fuel duty reductions in a joint report in April 2014. This research can be found here: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/analysis-of-the-dynamic-effects-of-fuel-duty-reductions.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-01T14:09:32.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385764/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385764/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-25","Fuels: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the positive economic benefits of lower fuel prices caused by the fuel duty freeze.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","4259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385765","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-01","<p>The majority of government borrowing is financed through the issuance of UK government bonds known as ‘gilts’ by the Debt Management Office (DMO) and as such, the majority of the government’s debt is held in gilts.</p><p> </p><p>The Treasury does not hold detailed information on the holders of gilts. Information on sectoral holdings of gilts is published on a quarterly basis by the Office for National Statistics (ONS).</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-07-01T14:11:45.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385765/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385765/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-25","Public Sector Debt","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the national debt, from which individuals or organisations has the money been borrowed; and to whom or to which organisations is the debt owed.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","4358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385766","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-01","<p>The gross value of the Bank of England’s quantitative easing, the Asset Purchase Facility (APF), is included in the calculation of Public Sector Net Debt as a liability on the Bank’s balance sheet.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This inclusion of the APF is shown as part of Table 8D of the Public Sector Finances release jointly published by the independent Office for National Statistics and HM Treasury.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-07-01T14:13:43.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385766/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385766/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-25","Public Sector Debt","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the gross value of sterling issued through the Government's quantitative easing initiation is included in calculations of the national debt.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","4359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385767","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-02","<p>The monthly Public Sector Finances bulletin is published jointly by the independent Office for National Statistics and HM Treasury. The Public Sector Finances statistical release provides detail on how debt is calculated in Table 8A for Central Government and subsequent tables for the wider Public Sector as a whole.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-07-02T15:31:21.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385767/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385767/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-25","Public Sector Debt","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, on what basis the national debt is calculated.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","4360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385768","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>I refer the Rt Hon Gentleman to my comments during the Westminster Hall debate on Tuesday 17<sup>th</sup> December 2013.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-30T15:41:26.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385768/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385768/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-25","Sixth Form Colleges: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will amend the VAT status of sixth form colleges so that they are treated the same as academies, free schools, university technical colleges and schools.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","4349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385769","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-03","<p>As the Chancellor has said, we should not underestimate the impact that a Greek exit from the euro area would have on the European economy – or the knock-on effects on the UK. But the economic plan we’ve pursued in Britain these last five years has increased our resilience – and we will take whatever further steps are needed to protect the UK from new risks to our economic security.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-03T12:29:57.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385769/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385769/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-25","Economic Situation: Greece","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the potential implications for the UK economy are of Greece leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","4326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385770","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-01","<p>The government is committed to supporting families on low incomes, including through Tax Credits and the new Universal Credit. Universal Credit will significantly simplify the benefits system for claimants, and ensure that it always pays to be in work and to work more.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Rates of these benefits, including the child element in Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit, are available via .gov.uk</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-01T14:07:02.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385770/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385770/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-25","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans that the child element of child tax credit and the child element of universal credit will remain the same while universal credit is rolled out.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","4306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385771","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-03","<p>The total amount that local authorities received in (a) England, (b) Lancashire County Council and (c) Pendle (payment made on the basis of Pendle Borough Council boundaries) under the New Homes Bonus in each year since 2011 is set out in the attached table . This includes payment of the Bonus for previous delivery.<br><br></p><p><br><br></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-03T13:04:26.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385771/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385771/answer","PQ 4317.docx","PQ 4317.docx","New Homes Bonus Table","New Homes Bonus Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385771/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-25","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much local authorities received in (a) England, (b) Lancashire and (c) Pendle constituency under the New Homes Bonus in each year since 2011.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","4317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385772","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-03","<p>We are ready to have conversations with any area about their proposals for devolving powers and for the strong and accountable governance to support such powers, including governance proposals involving changes to local authority boundaries.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2015-07-03T12:56:39.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385772/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385772/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385772/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-25","Local Government: Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether as part of a city region devolution existing local authority boundaries can be varied where a case is made for doing so.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","4256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385773","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-03","<p>The independent Local Government Boundary Commission for England may undertake a principal area boundary review at the request of a local council or the Secretary of State, or on their own initiative.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-03T13:00:17.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385773/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385773/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385773/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-25","Local Government: Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the Local Government Boundary Commission can initiate a boundary review of a local authority in response to public representations without direct instruction from the Secretary of State or a request from the local authority in question.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","4257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385774","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-03","<p>I refer the rt. hon. Member to the speech given by my rt. hon. friend the Chancellor of the Exchequer in Manchester on 14 May, where he explained that when we transfer major powers to cities these must come with new city wide elected mayors who work with local councils.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2015-07-03T13:01:56.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385774/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385774/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385774/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-25","Mayors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his policy is on the structure of the relationship between metro mayors and local authorities.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","4225"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385775","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Department did not receive the original letter. A duplicate has now been received and will be replied to in due course.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-02T15:41:24.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385775/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385775/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when he intends to reply to the letter to him dated 14 May 2015 from the right hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton with regard to Ms P Hamilton.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","4226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385776","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Government remains committed to seeing an improvement in the provision of access services for video-on-demand (VoD) services. We have been monitoring progress of the provision of access services for VoD content since 2013 through engagement with the Authority for Television On Demand (ATVOD), platform operators and content providers. If ATVOD's 2015 annual survey of VoD services indicates that significant progress has not been made then, as stated in the Connectivity, Content and Consumers Paper (July 2013), we will consider legislation in 2016.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","3953","2015-07-02T10:49:13.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385776/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385776/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Video on Demand","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to improve the provision of access services for on-demand content.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","4223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385778","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Government has allocated £7.46 million to the Leicestershire broadband project. 31,388 homes and businesses had been given access superfast broadband by 31 March 2015 as a result of the project.</p><p> </p><p>Superfast broadband will become available to parts of the Seagrave area from late 2016 onwards. The Thrussington area is at planning and survey stage. Superfast broadband is expected in parts of the area by the end of December 2015. More details can be found on the Superfast Leicestershire website: <a href="http://www.superfastleicestershire.org.uk/when-and-where/" target="_blank">http://www.superfastleicestershire.org.uk/when-and-where/</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-02T15:40:40.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385778/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385778/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385778/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Broadband: Charnwood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans his Department has to ensure roll-out of superfast broadband to (a) Seagrave and (b) Thrussington in Charnwood.","false","Biography information for Edward Argar","Charnwood","Edward Argar","4254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385779","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Department received a total of 153 response to the consultation launched in February 2015 on the reform of the Electronic Communications Code, my officials are currently analysing these responses and I will respond to Parliament as soon as possible.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-30T14:56:34.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385779/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385779/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385779/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Telecommunications: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when his Department will be publishing a response to its consultation on Reforming the Electronic Communications Code launched on 26 February 2015.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","4384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385780","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Government remains committed to seeing an improvement in the provision of access services for video-on-demand (VoD) services. We have been monitoring progress of the provision of access services for VoD content since 2013 through engagement with the Authority for Television On Demand (ATVOD), platform operators and content providers. If ATVOD's 2015 annual survey of VoD services indicates that significant progress has not been made then, as stated in the Connectivity, Content and Consumers Paper (July 2013), we will consider legislation in 2016.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-02T15:39:40.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385780/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385780/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385780/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Video on Demand: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will review the effectiveness of existing legislation on subtitles and audio description for on-demand television.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","4378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385781","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>We have been monitoring progress of the provision of access services for Video on Demand (VoD) content since 2013 through engagement with the Authority for Television on Demand (ATVOD), platform operators and content providers. As part of our continuing assessment of access to such services for VoD content, we will use information from a variety of sources and engagement with relevant parties to develop a target that we would expect to see reached by mid-2016.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-02T15:38:29.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385781/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385781/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Video on Demand: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions he has had with television representatives on the setting of targets on the provision of subtitles for on-demand television services.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","4379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385782","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-14","<p>Government recognises the importance of Digital Inclusion. The Government Digital Service launched the Government’s Digital Inclusion Strategy in April 2014. The Strategy sets out 10 actions that Government and partners from the public, private and voluntary sector will take to reduce digital exclusion.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-14T14:19:04.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385782/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385782/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Digital Technology: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he plans to take to reduce the digital exclusion of people with sensory loss.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","4377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385783","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>I have made no assessment to date. It is for the relevant local bodies to assess the impact that the individual stages of the Tour of Britain have had on local economies.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-02T07:30:32.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385783/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385783/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-25","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department has made of the effect to a local economy of hosting the Tour of Britain.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","4396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385784","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-02","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 12 June 2014 to Question 199115 to the hon. Member for Moray (Mr Robertson).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-02T15:05:18.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385784/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385784/answer","20140612 - Q n A extract on Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft.doc","20140612 - Q n A extract on Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft.doc","199115 - QnA extract on JSF Aircraft","199115 - QnA extract on JSF Aircraft","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385784/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-25","Aircraft Carriers: Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the design of the Queen Elizabeth Class carrier decks has had to be adjusted to accommodate the heat produced by the F-35B lift fans.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","4370"
