"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385443","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-03","<p>National planning guidance for renewable energy underlines that the views of local communities likely to be affected should be listened to and states that it is important that their planning concerns are properly heard in matters that directly affect them. Local councils working with their communities are able to set out in their Local Plan where developments for renewable energy such as solar farms should and should not take place.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-07-03T13:09:54.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385443/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385443/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-24","Solar Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to his statement of 22 June 2015, Official Report, columns 617-9, whether local people will have the final say on planning applications for solar farms.","false","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","4206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385444","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-29","<p>The expected impact over the forecast period of the changes made to private pensions taxation as announced at Budget 2014 can be found in Table 2.1 (p.56) of the Budget 2014 document here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/293759/37630_Budget_2014_Web_Accessible.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/293759/37630_Budget_2014_Web_Accessible.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Following a consultation period the Chancellor made subsequent announcements relating to this measure. The Exchequer impact of these can be found in Table 2.1 (p.65) of the Autumn Statement 2014 document here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382327/44695_Accessible.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382327/44695_Accessible.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Monthly assessments of additional tax revenue from savers choosing to access their pensions flexibly are not available.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","4212","2015-06-29T15:42:20.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385444/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385444/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-24","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent estimate he has made of the additional tax revenue from savers choosing not to annuitise their retirement savings following the pensions flexibilities introduced on 6 April 2015 in (a) 2015, (b) 2016, (c) 2017, (d) 2018 and (e) 2019.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","4211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385445","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-29","<p>The expected impact over the forecast period of the changes made to private pensions taxation as announced at Budget 2014 can be found in Table 2.1 (p.56) of the Budget 2014 document here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/293759/37630_Budget_2014_Web_Accessible.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/293759/37630_Budget_2014_Web_Accessible.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Following a consultation period the Chancellor made subsequent announcements relating to this measure. The Exchequer impact of these can be found in Table 2.1 (p.65) of the Autumn Statement 2014 document here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382327/44695_Accessible.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382327/44695_Accessible.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Monthly assessments of additional tax revenue from savers choosing to access their pensions flexibly are not available.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","4211","2015-06-29T15:42:20.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385445/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385445/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-24","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent estimate he has made of the additional tax revenue from savers choosing not to annuitise their retirement savings following the pensions flexibilities introduced on 6 April 2015 in (a) April 2015, (b) May 2015 and (c) June 2015.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","4212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385446","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-29","<p>Pension Wise provides free and impartial guidance on what consumers can do with their pension pots, helping them make a decision which best suits their personal circumstances. The guidance encourages customers to think about how they can best provide for themselves in the future, and prompt them to think about how long their money needs to last.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of this, Pension Wise helps people understand when professional financial advice could be useful and how to access it by referring them to the Money Advice Service’s new Retirement Advisor Directory. The Directory helps people find a local advisor which serves their pot size, can provide a specialist type of retirement advice service, and displays information on whether they charge a minimum fee.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The government believes that it is vital that consumers should have access to professional financial advice if they need it, and supports the work of the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) to encourage the development of affordable models of advice to help service this need.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-29T15:30:52.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385446/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385446/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-24","Pensions: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the availability and affordability of professional advice for those wishing to draw down their retirement income.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","4209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385447","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-02","<p>The government is closely monitoring the operation and effectiveness of the Pension Wise service. This ongoing monitoring is part of a wider programme of evaluation that the government is undertaking to ensure that Pension Wise is working effectively, delivers value for money, and meets consumer needs.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-07-02T15:28:50.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385447/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385447/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-24","Pensions: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to (a) review the effectiveness of the Pension Wise service and (b) publish that review.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","4210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385448","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>Good progress is being made on the introduction of the Union flag on all driving licences issued to drivers in England, Scotland and Wales. I am confident that DVLA are on track to deliver this in the future.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-29T15:54:33.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385448/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385448/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Driving: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress he has made on putting a Union flag on all new and renewed driving licences.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","4155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385449","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>I have today placed in the Library a copy of the relevant sections of minutes of meetings held between 2010 and 2015 by the Public Health England Advisory Committee on Malaria Prevention, at which a Ministry of Defence representative was present, in relation to the use of mefloquine (commercial name Lariam).</p><p><br>Following an extensive search by officials, that concluded on 22 June 2015, it is apparent that the Department does not hold any correspondence between Public Health England and the Ministry of Defence on hallucinations, psychosis or suicidal thoughts in personnel prescribed mefloquine.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","4195","2015-06-29T16:05:10.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385449/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385449/answer","Mefloquine PQ 26 06 15final[1].pdf","Mefloquine PQ 26 06 15final[1].pdf","4194 - Relevant minutes of meetings of PHE and MOD","4194 - Relevant minutes of meetings of PHE and MOD","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385449/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-24","Armed Forces: Mefloquine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 126 and the Answer of 24 June 2015 to Question 2877, if he will place in the Library the (a) correspondence and (b) minutes of meetings between 2010 and 2015 between his Department and Public Health England Advisory Committee on malaria prevention in relation to the use of Lariam or Mefloquine and reports of (i) hallucinations, (ii) psychosis and (iii) suicidal thoughts in personnel prescribed those medications.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","4194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385450","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>I have today placed in the Library a copy of the relevant sections of minutes of meetings held between 2010 and 2015 by the Public Health England Advisory Committee on Malaria Prevention, at which a Ministry of Defence representative was present, in relation to the use of mefloquine (commercial name Lariam).</p><p><br>Following an extensive search by officials, that concluded on 22 June 2015, it is apparent that the Department does not hold any correspondence between Public Health England and the Ministry of Defence on hallucinations, psychosis or suicidal thoughts in personnel prescribed mefloquine.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","4194","2015-06-29T16:05:10.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385450/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385450/answer","Mefloquine PQ 26 06 15final[1].pdf","Mefloquine PQ 26 06 15final[1].pdf","4194 - Relevant minutes of meetings of PHE and MOD","4194 - Relevant minutes of meetings of PHE and MOD","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385450/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-24","Armed Forces: Mefloquine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 126 and the Answer of 24 June 2015 to Question 2877, when he became aware that he had no correspondence between Public Health England and his Department on hallucinations, psychosis or suicidal thoughts in personnel prescribed Mefloquine or Lariam; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","4195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385451","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Information on the number of continence advisors employed in the National Health Service is not collected by the Department.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-07-03T13:26:13.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385451/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385451/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Incontinence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many continence advisors were employed in the NHS in each year since 2005; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","4127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385452","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Information is not held centrally on the annual cost or amount of unused or unnecessary medicines in the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department commissioned the York Health Economics Consortium and the School of Pharmacy at the University of London to carry out research to determine the scale, causes and costs of waste medicines in England. The report, <em>Evaluation of the Scale, Causes and Costs of Waste Medicines</em>, was published in November 2010 and is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://eprints.pharmacy.ac.uk/2605/1/Evaluation_of_NHS_Medicines_Waste__web_publication_version.pdf" target="_blank">http://eprints.pharmacy.ac.uk/2605/1/Evaluation_of_NHS_Medicines_Waste__web_publication_version.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This found that the gross cost of unused prescription medicines in primary and community care in the NHS in England in 2009 was estimated to be £300 million a year and that up to £150 million of this was avoidable.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>A number of initiatives, led by NHS England, are currently underway to optimise the use of medicines in the NHS and better empower patients.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-07-03T13:19:43.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385452/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385452/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Prescription Drugs: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the annual cost of destroyed unused prescribed medication; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","4128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385453","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>This information is not collected.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>While the Hospital Episode Statistics accident and emergency (A&amp;E) data set does contain information about the diagnosis of patients attending A&amp;E, it is not possible to identify the conditions requested as the diagnosis system in place is not detailed enough to classify these conditions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table 14 in the Health and Social Care Information Centre’s (HSCIC’s) annual publication demonstrates the diagnosis groupings published. Data for 2013/14 can be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB16728/acci-emer-atte-eng-2013-14-data.xlsx" target="_blank">http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB16728/acci-emer-atte-eng-2013-14-data.xlsx</a></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-03T11:42:59.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385453/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385453/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Accident and Emergency Departments: Genito-urinary Medicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of attendances at A&E because of (a) urinary tract infections, (b) catheter-related infections and (c) stoma care issues in each of the last three years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","4129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385454","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Government’s 2011- 2015 Affordable Homes Programme exceeded expectations, delivering nearly 186,000 affordable homes since April 2011, about 16,000 more than originally planned.<br><br>£38 billion of public and private investment will help ensure 275,000 new affordable homes are provided between 2015 and 2020. This means we will build more new affordable homes than during any equivalent period in the last twenty years.<br><br></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-29T13:09:46.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385454/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385454/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-24","Affordable Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps the Government is taking to increase the number of affordable rented homes.","false","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","4208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385455","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>Many clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are already working with local partners to develop local transformation plans for children and young people’s mental health and wellbeing. They are receiving advice and support from Clinical Networks, Public Health England and the learning collaboratives delivering the Children and Young People’s Improving Access to Psychological Therapies service transformation programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England and partners will be developing further resources and support over the summer which will be available both to CCGs and partner organisations to build on their initial plans in the medium and long term to achieve the ambition set out in <em>Future in Mind (March 2015) </em>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This ambition is based on what children and young people, their families and the professionals who support them said would improve children and young people’s mental health and wellbeing.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The letter of 25 May referred to in response to <em><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-17/2995/" target="_blank">Question 2995</a></em> informed CCGs that access to new funds would be linked to the development of local transformation plans. NHS England plans to publish the guidance for transformation plans in July. In parallel with this, all CCGs will be given a share of the additional funding for children and young people’s mental health for 2015/16 to support their effort to develop a local transformation plan.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","4201 ; 4202","2015-06-29T13:41:41.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385455/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385455/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015 to Question 2995, how his Department will support clinical commissioning groups to improve a transformation plan ruled inadequate.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","4200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385456","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>Many clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are already working with local partners to develop local transformation plans for children and young people’s mental health and wellbeing. They are receiving advice and support from Clinical Networks, Public Health England and the learning collaboratives delivering the Children and Young People’s Improving Access to Psychological Therapies service transformation programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England and partners will be developing further resources and support over the summer which will be available both to CCGs and partner organisations to build on their initial plans in the medium and long term to achieve the ambition set out in <em>Future in Mind (March 2015) </em>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This ambition is based on what children and young people, their families and the professionals who support them said would improve children and young people’s mental health and wellbeing.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The letter of 25 May referred to in response to <em><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-17/2995/" target="_blank">Question 2995</a></em> informed CCGs that access to new funds would be linked to the development of local transformation plans. NHS England plans to publish the guidance for transformation plans in July. In parallel with this, all CCGs will be given a share of the additional funding for children and young people’s mental health for 2015/16 to support their effort to develop a local transformation plan.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","4200 ; 4202","2015-06-29T13:41:41.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385456/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385456/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015 to Question 2995, how his Department will support clinical commissioning groups to help them fulfil their transformation plans.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","4201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385457","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>Many clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are already working with local partners to develop local transformation plans for children and young people’s mental health and wellbeing. They are receiving advice and support from Clinical Networks, Public Health England and the learning collaboratives delivering the Children and Young People’s Improving Access to Psychological Therapies service transformation programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England and partners will be developing further resources and support over the summer which will be available both to CCGs and partner organisations to build on their initial plans in the medium and long term to achieve the ambition set out in <em>Future in Mind (March 2015) </em>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This ambition is based on what children and young people, their families and the professionals who support them said would improve children and young people’s mental health and wellbeing.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The letter of 25 May referred to in response to <em><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-17/2995/" target="_blank">Question 2995</a></em> informed CCGs that access to new funds would be linked to the development of local transformation plans. NHS England plans to publish the guidance for transformation plans in July. In parallel with this, all CCGs will be given a share of the additional funding for children and young people’s mental health for 2015/16 to support their effort to develop a local transformation plan.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","4200 ; 4201","2015-06-29T13:41:42.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385457/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385457/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015 to Question 2995, what plans he has to allocate funding for children and young people's mental health service transformations to those clinical commissioning groups who do not produce a transformation plan.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","4202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385458","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-30","<p>The programme remains fully committed and £838,959,958 has been paid out from the European Regional Development Fund since 1 May 2010 and £526,182,985 remains to be claimed by grant recipients. We have extended some project activity into the autumn to ensure that opportunities to spend remaining funds are maximised by the deadline of the end of December 2015.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-06-30T11:09:36.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385458/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385458/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-24","European Regional Development Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Answer of 26 March 2015 to Question 225021, what proportion of funds under the 2007-13 European Regional Development Fund which were committed after May 2010 have not yet been drawn down; and whether he expects the full amount to be drawn down before the September 2015 deadline.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","4161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385459","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Answer to Question 2124 stated that the savings announced on 4 June arise where beneficiaries from RGF Rounds 1-5 had, by mutual agreement, not drawn down the full amount that was made available to them. I am not able to list each of the beneficiaries which did not draw down the full amount as this information is commercially confidential.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-30T16:21:02.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385459/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385459/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Regional Growth Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 17 June 2015 to Question 2126, if he will list each of the beneficiaries under the Regional Growth Fund which did not draw down the full amount in each (a) region and (b) Regional Growth Fund bidding round.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","4158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385460","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>Rothschild will be paid a fee of £25k for their work on the disposal of the Government’s shareholding in Royal Mail. Each of the banks who executed the Accelerated Bookbuild were paid £1. Freshfields fees for the sale are expected to be around £50k.<br></p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-30T16:04:32.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385460/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385460/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015 to Question 2810, what non-discretionary fees and payments were paid to each of those firms.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","4159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385461","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>A decision will be made soon on the payment of the discretionary payment. That decision will be made in the context of the letter of engagement with the banks.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-30T16:08:46.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385461/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385461/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 16 June 2015 to Question 1837, when he plans to make a decision on whether the discretionary fee will be paid; what framework he has set for making that decision; and on what consideration it will be based.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","4160"
