"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385465","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-02","<p>As the Government has made clear, it is important that we address the concerns of the British people about the EU. Part of that means reforming welfare to reduce the incentives that have encouraged migration from Europe.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-02T13:45:07.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385465/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385465/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Welfare Tax Credits: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of whether the introduction of a mandatory four-year contributory period applied to both UK and EU nationals prior to eligibility for the tax credit element of universal credit would be permissible under EU law.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","4119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385466","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-01","<p>Local authorities are able to gather information for the purposes of council tax administration under existing legislation, and this could potentially include information on tenure. Decisions on what information can legally be gathered are a matter for local authorities.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-01T15:39:51.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385466/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385466/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-24","Council Tax: Forms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether there are any barriers or regulations that prevent local authorities from requesting details of a person's tenure on council tax registration forms.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","3946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385467","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-02","<p>'Ever Closer Union' has been directly referenced in 23 cases of the Court of Justice of the European Union since 2005. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), has been clear that ever closer union might be right for some, but it is not right for Britain.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-02T14:50:42.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385467/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385467/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effects on the implementation of EU law in the UK of removing the words ever closer union from the preamble to the EU Treaties on Article 1 of the Treaty on European Union.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","4003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385468","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-03","<p>Twenty three judgments, opinions or orders of the Court of Justice and the General Court have contained references to “ever closer union” since 2005.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-03T13:15:28.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385468/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385468/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what information his Department holds on how many European Court of Justice cases have cited the words Ever Closer Union from the preamble to the EU Treaties and Article 1 of the Treaty on European Union in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","4004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385469","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Edinburgh Agreement addressed specific Danish concerns with the Maastricht Treaty. Those parts of the Agreement that remained relevant following the 1997 Treaty of Amsterdam were reflected in the EU Treaties by means of a protocol which is binding on the European Court of Justice and on the Member States.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-06-30T15:07:27.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385469/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385469/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what effect the 1992 Edinburgh Agreement had on the application of EU treaties in the UK; and whether it is his Department's assumption that the European Court of Justice is obliged to follow the provisions of that Agreement.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","4123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385470","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-03","<p>The purpose of Council Decision 2009/857/EC on the implementation of Article 16(4) of the Treaty on European Union is to allow Member States that are close to but do not constitute a blocking minority to request that the Council defer adoption of a measure for a period of time to allow for further discussions with a view to resolving the concerns that they have raised. It came into effect with the introduction of the changed system of calculating a Qualified Majority on 1 November 2014. Although the Government does not keep data on this provision, to the best of our knowledge it has not been invoked.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-03T13:17:32.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385470/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385470/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many times the procedure provided for in Council Decision 2009/857/EC on the implementation of Article 16(4) of the Treaty on European Union has been invoked in each of the years since that Decision entered force; what the concerns of the member states that invoked the procedure were in each such case; and how those concerns were met in the final decision taken in each such case.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","4126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385471","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-02","<p /> <p>The information is not available. The Department published its strategy for releasing official statistics on Universal Credit in September 2013. As outlined in the strategy, officials are quality assuring data for Universal Credit and formulating a definitive list of what statistics will be provided in the future.</p><p> </p><p>These statistics will be published in accordance with the relevant protocols in the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-02T13:53:25.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385471/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385471/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Universal Credit: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of EU nationals is eligible for universal credit in those areas in which that benefit is being trialled.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","4120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385472","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-02","<p /> <p>EU national workers have access to the same range of support as UK nationals.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-02T13:59:54.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385472/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385472/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Minimum Wage: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what forms of local and central government support are available to an EU national working on the minimum wage other than tax credits.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","4122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385473","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Government committed in its 2015 manifesto to “designate a further protected area at Ascension Island, subject to the views of the local community”. Consideration is currently being given to all options for marine management around Ascension Island. Any decision will be based on scientific justification, financial viability, effective enforcement and monitoring.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-06-29T12:28:02.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385473/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385473/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","Ascension Island: Marine Protected Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will take steps to designate a marine protected area around Ascension Island.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","James Gray","3991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385474","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>The UK is committed to conserving Asian elephants and recognises the growing threats to their populations, particularly from poaching and cross-border, illegal trade in live animals to feed the demand by the tourist and entertainment industries. The UK has been working internationally through the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species (CITES) in discussion with elephant range states, including India, to increase protection for Asian elephants. We secured agreement in 2014 for elephant range states to put in place measures to prevent illegal trade in live elephants.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Darwin Initiative, a UK Government grants scheme that helps to protect biodiversity and the natural environment, has in the past contributed over £300,000 towards a five-year project in Assam, India, helping to mitigate human-elephant conflict. Indian organisations working on elephant protection will also be eligible to apply for funding under a second round of the Illegal Wildlife Trade Challenge Fund, part of the £13 million that the Government has made available to support action to tackle the illegal wildlife trade.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As a global leader on this issue, the UK Government hosted the London Conference on the Illegal Wildlife Trade in February 2014 and played a major role in the success of the follow-up conference in Botswana in March 2015. The UK Government has a broad and deep relationship with India on a wide range of issues, including biodiversity, and we look forward to working further with the Indian Government on the protection of the Asian elephant and other threats to biodiversity in that region.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-06-29T11:25:08.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385474/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385474/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Elephants: India","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to support the Indian government in protecting Asian elephants.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","James Gray","3992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385475","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-02","<p /> <p>The information available on the number of Employment and Support Allowance claimants can be found at: <a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users can be found at: <a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a>.</p><p> </p><p>However, information on the number of Employment and Support Allowance claimants who have had Social Fund deductions is not readily available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-02T13:45:47.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385475/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385475/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many employment and support allowance claimants there were in each year since 2010; and how many such claimants had Social Fund Loan payments deducted in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","4172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385476","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>The Department does not collect this information.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T16:31:19.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385476/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385476/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many employment and support allowance claimants had Social Fund Loan repayments wrongly deducted from their benefits in each year since 2010; and how many of those deductions were due to (a) prior full loan repayment and (b) non-existence of the loan.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","4173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385477","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-01","<p>The pathways through which antibiotic resistance genes can be transferred between bacteria of any origin or strain are complex.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to carry out research and surveillance to better assess the potential for, and the frequency of, spread of antibiotic resistance genes between bacteria, including between those of human and animal origin. Examples of recently commissioned or completed projects include:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>Potential risk to human and animal health from the emergence and spread of Beta-lactamase resistance in Great Britain.</li><li>Molecular signature of antibiotic resistance in pigs as a potential source of antibiotic resistance in humans.</li><li>Characterisation of ESBL/Amp C/ Carbapenam resistant E.coli from pigs and poultry to identify resistance genes, circulating plasmids and fitness attributes.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Final reports from completed projects are published via GOV.UK. Results from surveillance of resistance in key zoonotic bacteria are published annually in the Veterinary Antimicrobial Resistance and Sales Surveillance report.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4135","2015-07-01T11:32:48.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385477/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385477/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what research her Department has commissioned on horizontal gene transmission between bacteria in the human gut which transfers antibiotic resistance from one organism to another regardless of its strain or of its human or animal origin.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385478","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-01","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation of our relationship with the EU. In addition, Defra is making the case for improvement to the Common Agricultural Policy so that it is simpler and more effective.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-01T12:15:20.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385478/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385478/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Agriculture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment her Department has made of the effect that withdrawal from the EU would have on British farming.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385479","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>This Government is committed to working with industry to develop a long-term plan to grow our food and farming industry. The plan will set out how British food and farming can become a world leader: innovative, competitive, profitable and resilient. Any future funding to deliver the plan will, as with all Government expenditure, be considered as part of the next Spending Review. It will build on the extensive support across Government for innovation and research, skills and apprenticeships, and export promotion.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-30T15:11:20.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385479/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385479/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what funding her Department has allocated to delivery of the Government's 25-year plan to grow, buy and sell more British food.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385480","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>Our immediate priority, over the next year, is to simplify the Common Agricultural Policy (CAP) Reducing the administrative burden of the CAP on farmers is a necessary part of increasing the competitiveness of our food and farming sector.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have pushed hard in the EU for reforms such as a review of the greening rules which place unnecessary burdens on farmers for limited environmental benefits. There is an opportunity to reform the CAP in a positive way for farmers by developing a simpler policy as part of the Commission’s CAP simplification programme.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-30T14:28:22.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385480/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385480/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Common Agricultural Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what her priorities are for reforming the Common Agricultural Policy; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385481","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government’s commitment to treble the number of apprenticeships in food, farming and agri-tech is a key part of the Government’s overall programme to increase apprenticeships, which is led and funded by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills. The future funding of apprenticeships will, as with all Government expenditure be considered as part of the next Spending Review. Our priority is to grow the number of apprenticeships and we will fund accordingly.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","3923","2015-06-30T14:41:04.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385481/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385481/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Agriculture: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what funding her Department plans to allocate to contributing to achieving the Government's target of three million more apprenticeships by expanding apprenticeships in the food, farming and agri-tech sector.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385482","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-07","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills publish data online showing Apprenticeship Programme Starts by Sector Framework, including agriculture, horticulture, animal care and food manufacture:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416508/apprenticeships-starts-by-sase-framework.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416508/apprenticeships-starts-by-sase-framework.xls</a></p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","3915","2015-07-07T16:21:41.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385482/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385482/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Agriculture: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate her Department has made of how many apprentices work in the food, farming and agri-tech sector.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385483","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-01","<p>The pathways through which antibiotic resistance genes can be transferred between bacteria of any origin or strain are complex.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to carry out research and surveillance to better assess the potential for, and the frequency of, spread of antibiotic resistance genes between bacteria, including between those of human and animal origin. Examples of recently commissioned or completed projects include:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>Potential risk to human and animal health from the emergence and spread of Beta-lactamase resistance in Great Britain.</li><li>Molecular signature of antibiotic resistance in pigs as a potential source of antibiotic resistance in humans.</li><li>Characterisation of ESBL/Amp C/ Carbapenam resistant E.coli from pigs and poultry to identify resistance genes, circulating plasmids and fitness attributes.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Final reports from completed projects are published via GOV.UK. Results from surveillance of resistance in key zoonotic bacteria are published annually in the Veterinary Antimicrobial Resistance and Sales Surveillance report.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4136","2015-07-01T11:32:48.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385483/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385483/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information her Department holds on the extend to which the presence of antibiotic resistant organisms in the human gut is the result of horizontal gene transmission from bacteria of farm animal origin, notwithstanding the strains of bacteria concerned.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385484","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>Officials of the Veterinary Medicines Directorate (VMD), an executive agency of Defra, meet regularly with the Responsible Use of Medicines in Agriculture Alliance (RUMA) and its member organisations. The VMD attends meetings of RUMA as an observer.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-29T14:14:55.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385484/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385484/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Responsible Use of Medicines in Agriculture Alliance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether Ministers and officials in her Department have met the Responsible Use of Medicines in Agriculture Alliance.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385485","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-03","<p>Resources for the financial years 2015-16 and 2016-17 have yet to be agreed. Government officials are currently developing the framework for delivering the blue-belt of marine conservation and protection across the Overseas Territories, which will be implemented on a case by case basis, dependent on local support and environmental need.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-07-03T11:07:49.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385485/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385485/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","Marine Conservation Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what resources he plans to allocate to put in place a marine blue belt around the Overseas Territories to protect marine habitats in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385486","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-30","<p>My officials are currently engaged with a number of interested parties, including colleagues in the Department for the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, in working up options as to the possible shape and scope of a pocket park programme. Budgets are yet to be determined.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-30T11:19:52.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385486/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385486/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-24","Parks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to launch his programme of pocket parks in towns and cities; and what budget he plans to allocate to that programme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385487","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government has made good progress on designating a Blue Belt of Marine Conservation Zones around our coasts. The first tranche of 27 Marine Conservation Zones was designated in 2013, and a consultation on 23 sites proposed for the second tranche closed in April this year. We will designate the second tranche by January 2016.</p><p> </p><p>We have committed to completing the network of Marine Conservation Zones, to create a Blue Belt of protected sites around our coasts. Further details on our plans to achieve this will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4096 ; 4097","2015-06-30T13:42:04.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385487/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385487/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Marine Conservation Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when she expects to complete the network of Marine Conservation Zones.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385488","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-03","The Government committed in its 2015 manifesto to, “designate a further protected area at Ascension Island, subject to the views of the local community.” The blue-belt of marine protection is a long term strategy for the conservation and protection of dynamic and important ecosystems across the Overseas Territories. Marine Protected Areas (MPAs), which could form part of the blue-belt of marine protection, are currently being considered around Pitcairn and Ascension Islands. Further designations will be similarly considered on a case by case basis, dependent on local support and environmental need.","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-07-03T11:10:40.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385488/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385488/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","Marine Conservation Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he plans to designate a marine blue belt around the Overseas Territories to protect marine habitats.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385489","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Animal and Plant Health Agency and Rural Payments Agency are working closely to develop proposals. Any decisions in this area will be announced by the Secretary of State when made.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4007 ; 4008","2015-06-29T13:15:19.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385489/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385489/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385489/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Farms: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when the Single Inspection Taskforce will be established; and what Departmental resources she will allocate to it in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385490","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government has made good progress on designating a Blue Belt of Marine Conservation Zones around our coasts. The first tranche of 27 Marine Conservation Zones was designated in 2013, and a consultation on 23 sites proposed for the second tranche closed in April this year. We will designate the second tranche by January 2016.</p><p> </p><p>We have committed to completing the network of Marine Conservation Zones, to create a Blue Belt of protected sites around our coasts. Further details on our plans to achieve this will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4089 ; 4097","2015-06-30T13:42:04.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385490/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385490/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Marine Conservation Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when she plans to designate the second tranche of Marine Conservation Zones.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385491","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government has made good progress on designating a Blue Belt of Marine Conservation Zones around our coasts. The first tranche of 27 Marine Conservation Zones was designated in 2013, and a consultation on 23 sites proposed for the second tranche closed in April this year. We will designate the second tranche by January 2016.</p><p> </p><p>We have committed to completing the network of Marine Conservation Zones, to create a Blue Belt of protected sites around our coasts. Further details on our plans to achieve this will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4089 ; 4096","2015-06-30T13:42:03.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385491/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385491/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385491/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Marine Conservation Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when she plans to designate the third tranche of Marine Conservation Zones.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385492","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-02","<p>The European Commission are responsible for negotiating international trade agreements on behalf of the European Union. However, the UK actively supported the inclusion of commitments on animal welfare in the agreement with Canada (CETA). We are also pressing strongly for the same in the EU/US Free Trade Agreement; and will be making the case in other agreements under negotiation, including those with Japan and Vietnam.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We will also work with the Commission and other trading partners, to incorporate EU animal welfare standards into the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE) international trade framework.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-02T16:04:50.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385492/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385492/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385492/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Animal Welfare: Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to ensure that high animal welfare standards are incorporated into international trade agreements; and how her Department plans to measure such standards.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385493","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-02","<p>Defra has responsibility for policy on national parks, areas of outstanding natural beauty (AONBs) and sites of special scientific interest (SSSIs), while oversight of the planning system and green belt protections are the policy responsibility of the Department for Communities and Local Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>a) The National Planning Policy Framework (NPPF) is clear that most types of new development in green belt are inappropriate, and should only be approved in very special circumstances. The Government published further guidance in October 2014, which reaffirmed the need to consider green belt protection when developing local plans. Policy also encourages the use of brownfield sites for development.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>b) A quarter of England is protected as national park or AONB, recognising the importance of conserving and enhancing our finest landscapes, their culture and heritage; and the contribution our beautiful countryside makes to the nation’s prosperity and well-being. The NPPF contains strong planning policies to maintain the protection of these landscapes on the nation’s behalf. These policies provide national parks, the Broads and AONBs with the highest status of protection in relation to landscape and scenic beauty.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>SSSIs are protected both by legislation and through the NPPF. Section 28 of the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981 (as amended) sets out provisions regarding the notification, protection and management of SSSIs, and requires authorities to take steps to further the conservation of SSSIs. The NPPF provides strong protection for SSSIs and for other environmental designations. It also directs planning authorities to give consideration to the conservation and enhancement of biodiversity in their decision making.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Existing protections for the green belt, for our national parks, and for other environmental designations are robust and this Government is committed to maintaining that protection.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-07-02T09:26:10.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385493/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385493/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Countryside","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans she has to (a) protect the Green Belt and (b) maintain national protections for Areas of Outstanding Natural Beauty, National Parks, Sites of Special Scientific Interest and other environmental designations.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385494","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-03","<p>In April 2014 and December 2014 respectively, the Government published monitoring data for the badger culls in 2013 and 2014 in Gloucester and Somerset. The Government plans to publish monitoring data for culling in subsequent years.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-03T13:54:19.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385494/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385494/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Bovine Tuberculosis: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will publish in full all monitoring data collected in each year of the badger culls in Gloucestershire and Somerset.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385495","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-03","<p>The Independent Expert Panel provided advice on the safety, effectiveness and humaneness of controlled shooting of free-ranging badgers, during the pilot phase which took place during a six-week period in 2013. We have since moved from piloting to implementation.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Natural England will continue to monitor this year’s culls. Monitoring will include compliance checks, and observing accuracy of shooting by new contractors. Effectiveness and progress in each cull area will continue to be monitored closely during the culls, and the police will continue to be closely involved to ensure shooting is carried out safely.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-03T13:57:51.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385495/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385495/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Bovine Tuberculosis: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she plans to take to ensure that she receives independent scientific advice on safety, effectiveness and humaneness for each year of the badger cull pilots in Gloucestershire and Somerset.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385496","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government plans to publish monitoring data for the third year of culling in Gloucestershire and Somerset, in line with the position for the first and second years. The Government is committed to our strategy to make England free of bovine TB, of which culling badgers in areas where the disease is rife is a key element.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-30T15:46:03.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385496/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385496/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she plans to take to ensure that monitoring data collected on the third year of the badger culls in Gloucestershire and Somerset is made available for independent scientific analysis; and what assessment she plans to make of that analysis as part of her decision on whether the culls should be extended to other areas.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385497","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-02","<p>Bacteria naturally adapt and find new ways to survive the effects of an antibiotic; any use of an antibiotic increases the risk that bacteria will develop resistance.</p><p> </p><p>The Government continues to carry out research and surveillance to better understand the link between antibiotic use and development of resistance. Final reports from completed research projects are published via gov.uk, while results from surveillance of resistance in key zoonotic bacteria are published annually in the Veterinary Antimicrobial Resistance and Sales Surveillance report.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-02T12:09:14.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385497/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385497/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department has made an assessment of the potential effect on the spread of antibiotic resistant strains of bacteria of increased use of antibiotics in farm animals; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385498","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Government collects sales data on antibiotics sold for use in animals. Currently there are no data sets that allow direct comparison between animal and human use of antibiotics in the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>For 2013; the current best estimate of total antibiotics dispensed for use in humans is 590 tonnes. Total antibiotics sold for use in animals was 420 tonnes, of which 355 tonnes were indicated for use in food producing animals, including fish.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Based on these data, antibiotics for food producing animals accounts for 35% of the total proportion of antibiotics in the UK.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-02T12:04:29.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385498/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385498/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385498/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information her Department holds on the proportion of antibiotic use in the UK which is accounted for by administration to animals on farms.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385499","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-07","<p>Data collected on antibiotics sold for use in animals does not show what an antibiotic was used for, or in how many animals it was administered.</p><p> </p><p>Antibiotics for administration through medicated feeding stuffs and water, which are typically used to treat livestock groups of any size, have accounted for, on average, 88% of total sales of veterinary antibiotics for the last six years.</p><p> </p><p>Regardless of administration route, antibiotics can only be prescribed by a veterinary surgeon following a clinical diagnosis.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-07T09:23:57.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385499/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385499/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385499/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Antibiotics: Animals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of the use of antibiotics in animals was accounted for by mass medication in the last six years.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385500","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>The annual progress report and implementation plan for the UK five Year Antimicrobial Resistance Strategy sets out our ambition for reducing antimicrobial use in livestock production over the next four years. The focus is on: improving bio-security and husbandry, optimising prescribing practices and improved education, training and public engagement.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4082","2015-06-29T13:43:27.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385500/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385500/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385500/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will set a target to reduce farm antibiotic use.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4080"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385501","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Advisory Committee on the Microbiological Safety of Food (ACMSF) sub-group on antimicrobial resistance (AMR) has been considering an assessment of the risk to consumers from MRSA in the food chain. Based on current evidence, the risk of contracting MRSA through consumption of foodstuffs is considered to be very low. This will be kept under review. Food Standards Agency food hygiene advice remains the same, i.e. that foodstuffs should be stored appropriately, handled hygienically and meat should be cooked thoroughly.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-29T14:32:47.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385501/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385501/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385501/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Pigmeat: MRSA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department has taken to investigate the implications for human health of the appearance of antibiotic resistant strains of MRSA in pig meat.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385502","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>The annual progress report and implementation plan for the UK five Year Antimicrobial Resistance Strategy sets out our ambition for reducing antimicrobial use in livestock production over the next four years. The focus is on: improving bio-security and husbandry, optimising prescribing practices and improved education, training and public engagement.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4080","2015-06-29T13:43:27.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385502/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385502/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385502/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will take measures to reduce farm antibiotics use.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","4082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385503","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-01","<p>The information requested is not collected by the Department. However, related information on reported accidents where a ‘distraction in vehicle’ contributory factor was allocated is published.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of reported personal injury road accidents by severity where a ‘distraction in vehicle’ contributory factor was allocated in the last five years is given in the following table:</p><p><strong><strong></strong></strong></p><p> </p><p><strong><strong></strong></strong></p><p> </p><p><strong><strong></strong></strong></p><p>Reported road accidents allocated a distraction in vehicle contributory factor, GB: 2009 - 2013</p><p><strong><strong></strong></strong></p><p> </p><p><strong><strong></strong></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p></td><td><p></td><td><p></td><td colspan="2"><p>Number of accidents</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Fatal</p></td><td><p>Serious</p></td><td><p>Slight</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p></td><td><p></td><td><p></td><td><p></td><td><p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>62</p></td><td><p>392</p></td><td><p>2,488</p></td><td><p>2,942</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>380</p></td><td><p>2,532</p></td><td><p>2,972</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>75</p></td><td><p>417</p></td><td><p>2,640</p></td><td><p>3,132</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>61</p></td><td><p>373</p></td><td><p>2,474</p></td><td><p>2,908</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>84</p></td><td><p>425</p></td><td><p>2,486</p></td><td><p>2,995</p></td></tr><tr><td><p></td><td><p></td><td><p></td><td><p></td><td><p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-01T15:16:36.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385503/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385503/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385503/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of traffic accidents in which the use of a satellite navigation system has been a contributing factor in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mark Tami","Alyn and Deeside","Mark Tami","3975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385504","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-03","<p>The UK is committed to supporting the Egyptian people’s aspiration for a full and functioning democracy, including an independent judiciary, a vibrant civil society and a free media. We urge Egypt to hold free and fair elections in which all parties can participate, as soon as possible.</p><p>I made a statement on 1 March encouraging Egypt to take the necessary steps to hold free and constitutional parliamentary elections as soon as possible and to complete the road map announced in July 2013.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-03T13:41:48.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385504/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385504/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385504/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-24","Egypt: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Egyptian counterpart on holding elections in that country.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","4145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385505","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>This is a matter for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government’s mandate to the NHS for 2015/16 and our publication <em>Achieving Better Access to Mental Health Services by 2020</em> both include a commitment to introduce tailored access and waiting times for mental health in 2015/16. We have invested a total of £120 million in this work.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Total mental health spending increased from £11.362 billion in 2013/14 to a planned £11.664 billion in 2014/15, a rise of £302 million.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-06-29T13:32:03.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385505/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385505/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385505/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Mental Health Services: St Helens South and Whiston","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to reduce waiting times for mental health patients in St Helens South and Whiston constituency.","false","Biography information for Ms Marie Rimmer","St Helens South and Whiston","Marie Rimmer","4167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385506","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The UK is a world leader in the extent and the quality of TV access services, which include subtitles, audio description and signing. UK broadcasters and content providers are committed to meeting the needs of disabled people and want to ensure that this remains the case in the future.</p><p> </p><p>Sections 303 to 305 of the Communications Act 2003 require Ofcom to draw up a Code which provides guidance as to the extent to which television services should provide access services. Ofcom monitors the provision of access services and publishes reports reflecting licensees’ performance against the target. Ofcom has the power to take action against broadcasters who fail to meet their target.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-02T15:44:05.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385506/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385506/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385506/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-24","Television: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions he has held with television broadcasters on improving services for people with sensory loss.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","4036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385507","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-14","<p>Government recognises the importance of Digital Inclusion. The Government Digital Service launched the Government’s Digital Inclusion Strategy in April 2014. The Strategy sets out 10 actions that Government and partners from the public, private and voluntary sector will take to reduce digital exclusion.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-14T14:22:06.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385507/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385507/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385507/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-24","Digital Technology: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will publish guidelines to encourage improvements in access to digital services for people with sensory loss.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","4034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385508","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Government is committed to ensure the quality of the access continues to improve. We have been monitoring progress of the provision of access services for Video on Demand (VoD) content since 2013 through engagement with the Authority for Television on Demand (ATVOD), platform operators and content providers. As part of our continuing assessment of access to such services for VoD content, we will use information from a variety of sources and engagement with relevant parties to develop a target that we would expect to see reached by mid-2016.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-02T10:50:42.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385508/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385508/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385508/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-24","Video on Demand: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the quality of access to on demand television content for people with sensory loss.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","4035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385509","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Public Health England’s (PHE) priority is to continue to raise public awareness of the signs and symptoms of cancer in England through the Be Clear on Cancer campaigns and to encourage people with those symptoms to see their general practitioner promptly. PHE is looking to understand and address inequalities in screening participation. A national workshop will be set up in the autumn to explore and share current knowledge and devise an action plan. The United Kingdom National Screening Committee (UK NSC) has also commissioned an evidence review on inequalities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Advisory Committee on Cervical Cancer will be reviewing the results from the Strategies to increase cervical screening uptake at first invitation (STRATEGIC) trial, an on-going trial to identify and implement key innovations to help engage uptake in young women who are entering the NHS Cervical Screening Programme at the age of 25. Further work will investigate the offer of self-sampling to non-attendees of all ages in the NHS Cervical Screening Programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In April 2012 the UK NSC gave its support for a pilot to assess the value of using human papilloma virus (HPV) testing as primary screening for cervical disease, rather than the currently used cytology test. The pilot is establishing the feasibility of using HPV as the primary screen for cervical disease in order to achieve better outcomes for women, while minimising over-treatment and anxiety, and whether it is practical to roll out nationally. The UK NSC will open a public consultation shortly on whether HPV as primary screening for cervical disease should replace the currently used cytology test.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","4052","2015-07-03T13:36:30.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385509/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385509/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385509/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Health Education: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the publication, Public Health England Marketing Strategy 2014 to 2017, what discussions he has had with Public Health England on its trial for improving screening uptake; and whether improving cervical screening uptake will form part of that trial.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","4053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385510","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Public Health England’s (PHE) priority is to continue to raise public awareness of the signs and symptoms of cancer in England through the Be Clear on Cancer campaigns and to encourage people with those symptoms to see their general practitioner promptly. PHE is looking to understand and address inequalities in screening participation. A national workshop will be set up in the autumn to explore and share current knowledge and devise an action plan. The United Kingdom National Screening Committee (UK NSC) has also commissioned an evidence review on inequalities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Advisory Committee on Cervical Cancer will be reviewing the results from the Strategies to increase cervical screening uptake at first invitation (STRATEGIC) trial, an on-going trial to identify and implement key innovations to help engage uptake in young women who are entering the NHS Cervical Screening Programme at the age of 25. Further work will investigate the offer of self-sampling to non-attendees of all ages in the NHS Cervical Screening Programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In April 2012 the UK NSC gave its support for a pilot to assess the value of using human papilloma virus (HPV) testing as primary screening for cervical disease, rather than the currently used cytology test. The pilot is establishing the feasibility of using HPV as the primary screen for cervical disease in order to achieve better outcomes for women, while minimising over-treatment and anxiety, and whether it is practical to roll out nationally. The UK NSC will open a public consultation shortly on whether HPV as primary screening for cervical disease should replace the currently used cytology test.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","4053","2015-07-03T13:36:30.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385510/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385510/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Health Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the publication, Public Health England Marketing Strategy 2014 to 2017, what discussions he has had with Public Health England on whether its plan to develop marketing campaigns to drive earlier diagnosis based on the Be Clear on Cancer campaign model will include a focus on raising awareness of cervical screening across the UK.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","4052"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385511","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-29","<p>My Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, meets the Foreign Secretary regularly on a whole range of issues. The Government has a clear mandate to improve Britain’s relationship with the rest of the European Union, and to reform the EU so that it creates jobs and increases living standards for all its citizens. The CBI and BCC have come out to say they support the reform agenda the PM is seeking to deliver. The Prime Minister is focused on success: he believes he can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-29T16:59:47.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385511/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385511/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385511/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with the Foreign Secretary on the potential effect on British companies of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","3993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385512","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-29","<p>The office to residential permitted development rights were introduced in May 2013 for a three year period. Our intention in bringing forward this relaxation was that it would act as a stimulus to economic growth and provide new homes. Use of the new right suggests there is great interest from owners and developers in undertaking residential conversions of office accommodation.</p><p> </p><p>I refer my hon. Friend to the Written Ministerial Statement of 25 March 2015, <em>Official Report, </em>Columns 131-138WS, (HCWS488), where we said that we would keep under review the case for extending the office to residential permitted development right, which is helping provide much needed new homes on brownfield land. This remains the case.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","4078","2015-06-29T13:07:50.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385512/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385512/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-24","Change of Use","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effect on the housing market of the expiration of permitted development rights in May 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen McPartland","Stevenage","Stephen McPartland","4156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385513","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-29","<p>The office to residential permitted development rights were introduced in May 2013 for a three year period. Our intention in bringing forward this relaxation was that it would act as a stimulus to economic growth and provide new homes. Use of the new right suggests there is great interest from owners and developers in undertaking residential conversions of office accommodation.</p><p> </p><p>I refer my hon. Friend to the Written Ministerial Statement of 25 March 2015, <em>Official Report, </em>Columns 131-138WS, (HCWS488), where we said that we would keep under review the case for extending the office to residential permitted development right, which is helping provide much needed new homes on brownfield land. This remains the case.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","4156","2015-06-29T13:07:50.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385513/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385513/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-24","Change of Use","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of properties that will not be completed upon the expiry of permitted development rights in May 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen McPartland","Stevenage","Stephen McPartland","4078"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385514","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Government will be appointing an independent chair for the review, and will make an announcement on this as soon as possible. It will be the responsibility of the chair to set out the timetable for conducting the review, which is due to report back to government by May 2016.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-07-02T11:08:28.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385514/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385514/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385514/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-24","Tickets: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will announce a timetable for the Independent Review into the secondary ticketing market.","false","Biography information for Stephen McPartland","Stevenage","Stephen McPartland","4125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385515","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>Information on the number of households affected by local authority, family type, and number of children can be found on Stat-Xplore, the Department’s online interactive tabulation tool, which can be accessed here:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T16:14:15.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385515/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385515/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385515/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Social Security Benefits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) households, (b) adults and (c) children have been affected by the benefit cap in each local authority area since the nationwide roll-out in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","4060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385516","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>We will publish a full Impact Assessment in due course. <strong> </strong></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T16:23:27.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385516/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385516/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385516/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he plans to publish an impact assessment on the reduction of the benefit cap.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","4061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385517","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-02","<p>I have been asked to reply as responsibility for this falls within the Ministry of Justice's remit.</p><p> </p><p>This is an internal Government review and we have not asked for submissions from the public. <br></p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-07-02T13:57:23.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385517/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385517/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385517/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-24","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which bodies his Department consulted on the terms of reference for the review of the employment tribunal fees regime.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","4085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385518","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-01","<p>Highways England is considering whether there are any potential safety improvements on the M56 between junctions 12 and 14 that should be included within its forward works programme. For example, a scheme to improve the westbound merge at junction 12 is currently being assessed to establish whether it would improve traffic flow and reduce the potential for accidents.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition, Highways England is undertaking work to update its route strategies and may identify further safety improvements for this section of motorway. In the longer term, these and other studies will inform Highways England’s considerations whether to upgrade the M56 to a smart motorway, which would further enhance its safety performance.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-01T14:53:50.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385518/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385518/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385518/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","M56: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 23 June 2015 to Question 3171, what steps his Department is taking to reduce accidents on the M56 between junctions 12 and 14.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","3947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385519","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-08","<p /> <p> </p><p>Jobcentre Plus work coaches are delivering a personalised service to best meet the needs of the claimant and the local labour market. The flexible model of support available through the Jobcentre Plus offer includes, Sector Based Work Academies, New Enterprise Allowance, Work Experience and access to skills provision.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>In addition, the Work Programme offers tailored support to those people who are at risk of becoming long-term unemployed.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-08T09:56:04.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385519/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385519/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385519/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-24","Employment: Torbay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to support claimants of benefits find employment in Torbay.","false","Biography information for Kevin Foster","Torbay","Kevin Foster","4084"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385520","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>We have received no such representations.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-03T11:46:03.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385520/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385520/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Human Fertilisation and Embryology (Mitochondrial Donation) Regulations 2015","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 18 June 2015 to Question 1960, what representations his Department has received from (a) other developed countries, (b) UN bodies, (c) EU institutions, (d) international health bodies and (e) international ethics bodies on the Human Fertilisation and Embryology (Mitochondrial Donation) Regulations 2015.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385521","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Local sexual health services and those that commission these services are best placed to assess the effectiveness of information and support available in their area.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-03T13:33:56.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385521/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385521/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Family Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2015 to Question 216, whether it is his policy that services provided by the Family Planning Association constitute sufficient social, medical and practical support for women experiencing unplanned pregnancies in the UK; and what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of social, medical and practical support for women experiencing unplanned pregnancies in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385522","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Our policy is that providers follow the guidance published in May 2014.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-03T13:32:10.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385522/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385522/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 18 June 2015 to Question 2148, whether it is his policy that a registered medical practitioner may form a good faith opinion for the purposes of section 1(1)(a) of the Abortion Act 1967 after having signed the statutory form HSA1.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385523","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Recording of NHS number on the HSA4 abortion notification form is not a statutory requirement.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","4131 ; 4132","2015-07-03T13:35:17.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385523/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385523/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to require every termination of pregnancy provider routinely to record a patient's NHS number.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385524","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-03T11:55:02.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385524/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385524/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average cost is to the NHS of an (a) medical and (b) surgical abortion when commissioned for delivery by the British Pregnancy Advisory Service.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385525","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Recording of NHS number on the HSA4 abortion notification form is not a statutory requirement.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","4131 ; 4133","2015-07-03T13:35:17.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385525/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385525/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many and what proportion of terminations of pregnancy commissioned for delivery in the private sector had NHS numbers missing from the patient's electronic record in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385526","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Prior to the 2015-16 financial year, the Family Planning Association (FPA) and Brook have received grant funding from the Department. All funding applications from voluntary sector organisations are assessed against a number of criteria, but Departmental policy clearly states that grants will not be awarded if there is any indication within the application that some or all of any funding awarded will be used to support political activities, including political lobbying activity. Up to April 2015, the Department had a contract with the FPA for a sexual health information service; this work has been extended for one year and is being managed by Public Health England. FPA’s contract excluded all lobbying activities. The British Pregnancy Advisory Service and Marie Stopes International receive no funding from the Department.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-03T13:31:05.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385526/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385526/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Family Planning: Lobbying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what measures are in place to prevent public funds paid to (a) the British Pregnancy Advisory Service, (b) Marie Stopes International, (c) the Family Planning Association and (d) Brook Charity from being used to support lobbying activities; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385527","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>Recording of NHS number on the HSA4 abortion notification form is not a statutory requirement.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","4132 ; 4133","2015-07-03T13:35:17.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385527/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385527/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether it is his policy not to record the NHS number for every termination of pregnancy contracted out by the NHS; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","4131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385528","Home Office","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Home Office does not routinely comment on individual cases. Where legally permissible we will deport foreign nationals to countries with the death penalty, provided the individual will not face the death penalty when they return.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-06-30T15:59:40.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385528/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385528/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385528/answer/previousversion/9778","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385528/answer/previousversion/9778",,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-24","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the status is of the Syrian refugee Raja Khouja and her husband Mahmoud Alhassan who are due to be deported to Saudi Arabia on 25 June 2015; and what her policy is on the deportation of individuals to countries which use the death penalty.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","3988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385529","Home Office","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Home Office is confident that the Independent Police Complaints Commission (IPCC) has the capacity to deliver its core functions and continues to be resourced adequately to deliver its expansion. The IPCC met its targets with regards to taking on a higher caseload in 2014/15 and is on course to meet its targets this year.</p><p>In February 2013, the Home Secretary committed to allocate further resource to the IPCC to allow it to investigate all serious and sensitive cases involving the police. This will be delivered as part of a wider change programme due to be completed by the end of 2017. In addition to the IPCC’s core budget, £18 million was allocated for this expansion in 2014/15 and £30 million for this year. Funding for future years will be determined in discussion with the IPCC.</p><p>The IPCC reports on its performance annually to Parliament. This report contains statistics on the number of investigations carried out each year. The IPCC’s annual reports can be found in the Library of the House.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","4011 ; 4012 ; 4013","2015-06-30T15:47:11.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385529/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385529/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-24","Independent Police Complaints Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the capacity of the Independent Police Complaints Commission (IPCC) to hold the police to account pursuant to its obligations under Section 1.5 of the IPCC Home Office Framework Agreement.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","4010"
