"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385605","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>Transport for London (TfL) publish information of recorded crimes on the TfL network in annual bulletins on a financial year basis. This information can be found on their website: <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/corporate/publications-and-reports/crime-and-incident-bulletins" target="_blank">https://tfl.gov.uk/corporate/publications-and-reports/crime-and-incident-bulletins</a></p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The number of incidents of the various crimes are in the attached table. TfL do not separate incidents that occur on London Underground and the Docklands Light Railway (DLR) so these are combined.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-29T14:23:46.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385605/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385605/answer","003976 - Table showing the number of incidents of various crimes.pdf","003976 - Table showing the number of incidents of various crimes.pdf","UIN 3976 - Table showing number of incidents","UIN 3976 - Table showing number of incidents","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385605/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Public Transport: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many incidents of (a) burglary, (b) criminal damage, (c) drugs, (d) fraud or forgery, (e) robbery, (f) sexual offences, (g) theft and handling, (h) violence against the person and (i) serious public disorder there were on (i) London Underground, (ii) London Overground, (iii) London buses, (iv) London tramlink and (v) the Docklands Light Railway in each year between 2008 and 2014.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","3976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385606","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>Following publication of the Better for Business report, the target date for achieving the reduction in guidance was set at May 2015. By that date Defra and its regulators had reduced guidance by 80%.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The project continues and we expect this figure to increase over the next few months. This reform enables businesses and the public to understand more easily what they have to do to comply with the law and to find this information more quickly, including guidance for farms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><br></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-29T13:37:02.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385606/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385606/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Farms: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to her Department's report, Better for Business, published in April 2014, what progress she made in cutting guidance to farms by 80 per cent by March 2015; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","4009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385607","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Animal and Plant Health Agency and Rural Payments Agency are working closely to develop proposals. Any decisions in this area will be announced by the Secretary of State when made.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4008 ; 4090","2015-06-29T13:15:19.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385607/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385607/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Farms: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress she has made on establishing the Farming Inspection Taskforce; and when she plans to make an announcement on that issue.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","4007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385608","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Animal and Plant Health Agency and Rural Payments Agency are working closely to develop proposals. Any decisions in this area will be announced by the Secretary of State when made.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","4007 ; 4090","2015-06-29T13:15:19.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385608/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385608/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Farms: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans she has to change the number of farm inspections in each year.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","4008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385609","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-29","<p>My written statement of 25 March provides full details of the legislative reforms delivered by Defra during the previous Parliament, about a third of which relate to agricultural regulations.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-29T14:19:02.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385609/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385609/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-24","Agriculture: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to the Answer of 30 June 2014 to Question 201927, what progress she has made on reforming the 516 agricultural regulations as part of the Red Tape Challenge.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","4193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385610","Prime Minister","false","2015-06-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-announces-new-taskforce-to-transform-child-protection" target="_blank">press release</a> issued by my office on 24 June 2015, which can be accessed via the gov.uk website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-06-30T16:48:35.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385610/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385610/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385610/answer",,,,,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-06-24","Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to the Answer of 24 June 2015 to the hon. Member for Bury St Edmunds, what the (a) objectives, (b) remit, (c) membership, (d) start date and (e) report date are of the task force chosen by the Secretary of State for Education; and whether he plans to publish the conclusions of that taskforce.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","3996"
