"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385614","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>Recreational deer stalking is not permitted on Ministry of Defence (MOD) land.</p><p>The MOD undertakes sustainable deer management ensuring that wild deer populations are both healthy and in balance with their environment</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-29T15:22:12.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385614/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385614/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-24","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether any deer stalking has been conducted on land owned by his Department since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385615","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Cabinet Secretary has replied to the hon. Member.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-06-29T16:08:27.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385615/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385615/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-24","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to respond to the letters from the hon. Member for North Durham dated 4 February 2015  and 28 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4075"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385616","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>Work is already underway on various options to improve compensation arrangements for passengers. The trial by c2c, starting in early 2016, of an automated system providing compensation for delays of between 2 and 29 minutes is very welcome, and it is exactly the kind of compensation system that puts passengers at the centre of the railway. Through franchising we will be working with other operators to ensure they offer a similar process for their customers.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-29T14:45:09.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385616/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385616/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Railways: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, from what date he expects to require train companies to improve compensation arrangements for passengers when trains are more than a few minutes late; what improvements to compensation arrangements he plans to make; and whether he has decided how many minutes late a train will have to be for passengers to claim compensation under this revised system.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385617","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>On the Midland mainline, better services can be delivered on that line before electrification using capacity and speed improvement works. We are pausing electrification works and a review has been commissioned from Sir Peter Hendy which will report in the autumn for how the rail upgrade programme will be carried out.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-29T13:03:45.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385617/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385617/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Midland Main Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to change the (a) extent and (b) scope of the Midland Main Line electrification project.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385618","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>As the Secretary of State announced on 25 June, in the House, the new chair of Network Rail has been asked to develop proposals for how the rail upgrade programme will be carried out. He is due to report to the Secretary of State for Transport in the Autumn.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-29T13:16:38.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385618/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385618/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if his Department will undertake an affordability review of Network Rail's enhancement projects.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385619","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>Departmental officials regularly meet with a range of stakeholders and representatives from across the rail industry, both within the UK and abroad.</p><p> </p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-06-29T14:41:38.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385619/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385619/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 23 June 2015 to Question 3117, whether any of those meetings took place outside the UK.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385620","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>We are working with the rail industry to introduce part-time season tickets during the course of this Parliament. This will enable operators to introduce their own products as soon as possible following the roll out of smart ticketing in 2016 and 2017. This will also enable us to consider their inclusion in future franchises.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-29T13:26:43.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385620/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385620/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-24","Railways: Season Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 10 June 2015 to Question 1318, when he expects that work with the rail industry to develop options for introducing part-time season tickets will be completed.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385621","Department of Health","false","2015-07-03","<p>National Health Service commissioners, including NHS England for its directly commissioned services, are legally required to fund drugs and treatments recommended in National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) technology appraisal guidance, normally within three months of the publication of NICE’s guidance.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-07-03T13:42:00.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385621/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385621/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-24","Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that recommendations by NICE on the availability of new drug treatments are fully implemented by NHS England.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","4139"
